WEBVTT

00:00.855 --> 00:03.172
<i>Here's what you missed on</i> Glee:
Kurt Hummel's back at McKinley!

00:03.224 --> 00:05.685
<i>Kurt's back at McKinley,</i>
<i>but he's still dating Blaine.</i>

00:05.695 --> 00:07.513
<i>Sam used to date Quinn,</i>
<i>but she's back with Finn,</i>

00:07.523 --> 00:08.738
<i>who used to date Rachel,</i>

00:08.748 --> 00:10.699
<i>who's still sort of in love</i>
<i>with him-- Finn, that is.</i>

00:10.750 --> 00:12.083
<i>Santana's in love</i>
<i>with Brittany,</i>

00:12.168 --> 00:13.401
<i>but she's too scared</i>
<i>to say it out loud--</i>

00:13.452 --> 00:14.568
But you told me
you were in love with me.

00:14.620 --> 00:15.903
I honestly don't know
what I was thinking.

00:15.955 --> 00:17.238
<i>And Britt's back</i>
<i>with Artie, anyways.</i>

00:17.289 --> 00:19.340
<i>Kids these days.</i>
I have a question.

00:19.408 --> 00:21.209
<i>Sue's bent on destroying the</i>
<i>Glee Club before Nationals.</i>

00:21.260 --> 00:22.627
Destroy the Glee Club!

00:22.712 --> 00:24.596
<i>She even formed an evil league</i>
<i>with nicknames.</i>

00:24.680 --> 00:26.414
The League of Doom.
I don't think I was listening

00:26.465 --> 00:28.508
when you said what our name was.
Is it League or Legion?

00:28.518 --> 00:30.031
Worst henchmen ever.

00:30.041 --> 00:31.611
<i>And that's what</i>
<i>you missed on</i> Glee!

00:34.273 --> 00:37.108
♪ Fondue for Two!
Fondue for Two! ♪

00:37.193 --> 00:38.526
♪ That's some hot dish! ♪

00:38.594 --> 00:40.445
♪ Fondue for Two! ♪

00:41.383 --> 00:43.284
Hi, I'm Brittany S. Pierce,

00:43.335 --> 00:46.137
and this is my new Internet
talk show, <i>Fondue for Two,</i>

00:46.221 --> 00:48.956
which combines the two things
I like most:

00:49.008 --> 00:51.342
hot cheese
and talking to people.

00:51.427 --> 00:55.346
My first two guests are
the school's biggest gossips,

00:55.431 --> 00:58.349
Mercedes Jones and
Ms. Tina Cohen-Chang.

00:58.434 --> 01:00.068
Shouldn't it be
<i>Fondue for Three?</i>

01:00.135 --> 01:03.988
Oh, my God, that is hot!

01:04.072 --> 01:06.157
Okay, so let's get down
to some hot dish.

01:06.241 --> 01:09.193
Um, I heard a rumor that
Mr. Kidney the janitor walks

01:09.278 --> 01:10.995
around school drinking vodka
out of a teapot.

01:11.063 --> 01:12.146
Is this really what they were

01:12.197 --> 01:13.247
doing in the '70s?

01:13.315 --> 01:14.999
Hot mess Mr. Kidney
aside, I want

01:15.084 --> 01:18.836
to talk about the rumor
about Asian men: not true.

01:18.921 --> 01:20.088
I mean, it's not even good.

01:20.155 --> 01:21.589
It tastes the way
a baby's diaper smells.

01:21.657 --> 01:23.491
I heard a rumor that Santana
plays for the other team,

01:23.542 --> 01:25.460
and I can confirm that rumor:
It's 100% true.

01:25.511 --> 01:27.495
Wait. What?

01:27.546 --> 01:29.180
Brittany, are you serious?

01:29.264 --> 01:30.848
Yes.
(cat meows)

01:30.933 --> 01:32.667
BRITTANY:
Look, it's Lord Tubbington.

01:32.718 --> 01:34.102
Hi!

01:34.169 --> 01:36.187
Hi. (smooches)

01:36.271 --> 01:37.438
This is Lord Tubbington.

01:37.506 --> 01:39.107
(baby talk):
Say hi to the camera.

01:39.174 --> 01:41.175
You want some cheese?

01:41.226 --> 01:42.343
That's disgusting.

01:42.394 --> 01:44.028
That's my baby.

01:44.113 --> 01:46.864
So, you're just gonna
gonna let him do that?

01:46.949 --> 01:49.990
Lord Tubbington's allowed to eat
cheese because he's on Atkins.

01:50.199 --> 01:52.734
Okay, well, that's all we have
time for today.

01:52.785 --> 01:55.203
Tune in next week
for <i>Fondue for Two.</i>

01:55.254 --> 01:58.106
We will be dipping raw meat
into boiling chocolate.

01:58.174 --> 01:59.274
♪ Fondue for Two! ♪

02:01.444 --> 02:03.421
(school bell rings)

02:03.621 --> 02:04.922
Hey.

02:05.006 --> 02:07.624
Why are you talking to me?
Can't I say hello?

02:07.709 --> 02:09.008
I guess. It's just Santana

02:09.077 --> 02:10.426
told me never
to speak alone with you

02:10.512 --> 02:12.379
because you would try
to steal all of my gold.

02:12.430 --> 02:16.183
Okay, uh... anyway,
I got you this.

02:16.250 --> 02:18.469
I know everyone's always
making fun of your lips,

02:18.553 --> 02:20.471
but I think they're cute
and worth weatherproofing.

02:20.538 --> 02:23.057
So, considering that
we're both single

02:23.108 --> 02:24.725
and I think your lips are cute,

02:24.776 --> 02:27.895
I was wondering if you would
go to to prom with me?

02:27.946 --> 02:29.146
As in your date?
Yeah.

02:29.214 --> 02:32.366
No.
No... "No, No" as in...?

02:32.433 --> 02:34.051
As in no prom.
Oh.

02:34.119 --> 02:35.435
I don't think I'm going.

02:35.487 --> 02:37.738
Are you worried
that Finn will be jealous?

02:37.789 --> 02:42.159
Look, you're just
not my type, okay, Rachel?

02:42.243 --> 02:45.245
So thanks for the lip chap.

02:47.677 --> 02:50.628
I feel like my life
finally has purpose.

02:50.680 --> 02:53.682
It's so nice to be a part of a
cause that's bigger than myself.

02:53.766 --> 02:56.151
Honey Badger, I am so thrilled,

02:56.235 --> 02:57.936
Can I ask why you're dressed
like David Bowie?

02:58.004 --> 02:59.187
I'm incognito.

02:59.272 --> 03:00.822
We're going deep
behind enemy lines.

03:00.906 --> 03:02.741
People are starting
to sense my weakness.

03:02.808 --> 03:04.743
They think I've
totally lost my grip.

03:04.810 --> 03:06.161
Can I help you?
Oh, yes.

03:06.245 --> 03:09.164
Can I have a hot tea, please?

03:09.248 --> 03:11.449
I'd just like a large cup
of mocha powder.

03:11.500 --> 03:12.951
David Bowie's incredibly
eccentric.

03:13.002 --> 03:14.753
Um, we don't take euros.

03:14.820 --> 03:17.756
So, Honey Badger, last week,
I had a revelation.

03:17.823 --> 03:19.424
Now, as you may
or may not know,

03:19.491 --> 03:20.658
the Middle East is in chaos.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.043
You know what started it all?

03:22.128 --> 03:23.828
No. A little Web site
called Wikileaks.

03:23.879 --> 03:25.213
You ever hear of them?

03:25.298 --> 03:27.515
Well, they let loose
with a couple of rumors.

03:27.600 --> 03:29.117
So I told Figgins

03:29.185 --> 03:31.219
I wanted to resuscitate
<i>The Muckraker.</i>

03:31.304 --> 03:33.288
But the school newspaper was
discontinued two years ago,

03:33.356 --> 03:35.506
due to lack of interest.

03:35.558 --> 03:37.559
The newspaper is making
a comeback at this school,

03:37.643 --> 03:38.860
and like print
newspapers everywhere,

03:38.928 --> 03:40.228
we're leaner
and meaner--

03:40.313 --> 03:43.281
no longer concerned
with facts, fact-checking,

03:43.349 --> 03:44.849
integrity or facts.

03:44.900 --> 03:46.985
<i>The Muckraker</i> motto?

03:47.036 --> 03:50.538
"If I heard it, it's probably
true or something."

03:50.623 --> 03:52.824
Sorry, but did you just
change disguises?

03:52.875 --> 03:55.026
I'm pretty sure that
barista's onto me.

03:55.077 --> 03:56.828
Now I'm Ann Coulter.

03:56.879 --> 04:00.048
As you may have noticed,
I'm coming slightly unhinged.

04:00.132 --> 04:01.699
Ohio loves you, Ann Coulter!

04:01.751 --> 04:04.702
That's better.
(sighs with relief)

04:04.754 --> 04:07.222
Can I make an observation?

04:07.306 --> 04:10.258
You're always trying to destroy
Will from inside the Glee Club.

04:10.343 --> 04:14.212
But I would like to try getting
him <i>out</i> of the Glee Club.

04:14.263 --> 04:18.733
Now, I was trolling the Internet
last night and I had an idea.

04:18.817 --> 04:20.517
I'll drink to that.

04:24.323 --> 04:26.891
(school bell ringing)

04:26.942 --> 04:28.827
Excuse me.

04:28.894 --> 04:31.413
Do you know
where a gal can find

04:31.480 --> 04:33.164
a pipin' hot cup of
Will Schuester?

04:33.468 --> 04:36.904
Oh, my God! April!

04:36.971 --> 04:38.606
What are you doing here?

04:38.657 --> 04:40.190
I thought you were on Broadway!

04:40.275 --> 04:44.311
I was! My all-white production of
<i>The Wiz</i> was a disaster.

04:44.362 --> 04:45.613
- Oh, April, I'm so sorry.
- Don't be!

04:45.664 --> 04:48.415
Being publicly humiliated
by the <i>New York Times</i>

04:48.483 --> 04:49.867
gets me to thinking--

04:49.951 --> 04:52.836
why am I weighing myself down
with the "Broadway classics"?

04:52.866 --> 04:54.175
I should just tell my own story.

04:54.205 --> 04:55.460
So I wrote the libretto

04:55.490 --> 04:58.425
to <i>Crossrhodes!</i>
<i>The April Rhodes Story.</i>

04:58.493 --> 04:59.627
You're writing a musical?

04:59.678 --> 05:01.629
Yep. That's why I'm here.

05:01.680 --> 05:04.965
So, Will, remember how
I bought you your auditorium?

05:05.016 --> 05:05.966
Oh, yeah.

05:05.996 --> 05:09.491
Well, I'm gonna need to borrow it
cause I'm running a little low on funds.

05:09.521 --> 05:12.222
Extra! Extra! Read all about it!

05:12.307 --> 05:14.341
Get your <i>Muckraker</i> here.

05:14.392 --> 05:15.943
Extra! Extra!
Get your <i>Muckracker</i> here!

05:16.010 --> 05:17.678
Hey. I think we should talk
about Nationals.

05:17.729 --> 05:19.279
We need to do a duet.

05:19.309 --> 05:20.702
I don't think that's a good idea.

05:20.732 --> 05:22.182
Why are you so concerned

05:22.233 --> 05:23.517
with Quinn's feelings

05:23.547 --> 05:25.290
when she obviously has
no interest in yours?

05:25.320 --> 05:26.537
What are you talking about?

05:26.621 --> 05:28.188
Haven't you read <i>The Muckraker?</i>

05:28.239 --> 05:29.573
It's our school's newspaper.

05:29.658 --> 05:33.043
Look at the "Blind Items" column.

05:33.073 --> 05:34.432
"What prom queen candidate is spending

05:34.462 --> 05:35.967
a lot of time in her closet?"

05:35.997 --> 05:37.669
Now that's garbage.
Quinn's claustrophobic.

05:37.699 --> 05:39.852
No, that's Santana. Read the next one.

05:43.588 --> 05:45.306
What the hell is this, dude?

05:45.373 --> 05:48.947
"What blondie former cheerleader is having
"a secret Moonlight Motel rendezvous

05:48.977 --> 05:51.232
- with another big-lipped blondie?"
- Where does it say that?

05:51.262 --> 05:52.734
Right on the front page
of the school newspaper!

05:52.764 --> 05:54.402
You don't seriously
believe this, do you?

05:54.432 --> 05:57.238
Well, why shouldn't I? Why wouldn't he
do the same thing that I did to him?

05:57.268 --> 05:58.123
Because it's gossip, Finn.

05:58.153 --> 05:59.820
This is your fault!

05:59.887 --> 06:01.739
You told everyone that I played

06:01.823 --> 06:04.758
for another team on your
ridiculous melted cheese show.

06:04.788 --> 06:06.531
Wait. Are you mad?
You <i>do</i> play for another team.

06:06.561 --> 06:09.417
You were on the Cheerios! And now
you're only in the New Directions.

06:09.447 --> 06:11.586
And you couldn't have thought
of any other way to say that?

06:11.616 --> 06:13.705
I swear I'm going to
punch your face off!

06:13.735 --> 06:15.873
Hey, you got a lot of nerve
accusing me of cheating

06:15.903 --> 06:18.209
when you're the one who
snuck in and stole my girl!

06:18.239 --> 06:20.061
Hey! Hey, Finn, where are you going?

06:20.091 --> 06:22.026
Hey, we got rehearsal! Not today!

06:29.017 --> 06:31.051
Dinner is served.

06:31.102 --> 06:32.970
(giggles)

06:33.054 --> 06:35.193
I thought you volunteered
to make dinner.

06:35.223 --> 06:37.524
Well, Mama drinks her dinner these days!

06:37.592 --> 06:38.842
Honk!

06:38.977 --> 06:41.895
Uh... (chuckles) can I be
blunt with you, April?

06:41.946 --> 06:43.084
(Glasses clink)

06:43.114 --> 06:47.501
I think any show about April Rhodes

06:47.569 --> 06:49.765
should be about your emotional journey.

06:50.739 --> 06:52.939
Oh.

06:52.991 --> 06:54.796
Hadn't really thought of that.

06:57.128 --> 06:59.267
I forget what a good
teacher you are, Will.

06:59.297 --> 07:02.716
Thanks.

07:02.784 --> 07:04.719
And lately, I don't feel like it.

07:04.753 --> 07:06.808
I mean, there's just so much drama in

07:06.838 --> 07:08.860
the Glee Club right
now-- more than usual.

07:08.890 --> 07:11.095
A lot of whispering and
backstabbing and love triangles

07:11.125 --> 07:13.761
and questions of sexuality--

07:13.812 --> 07:16.100
Sounds like your club's
got a touch of the Mac.

07:16.130 --> 07:17.898
The what? Fleetwood Mac?

07:17.965 --> 07:19.320
They fought all the time!

07:19.350 --> 07:21.635
There was affairs and divorces

07:21.686 --> 07:23.687
and whispers and gossip.

07:23.772 --> 07:26.110
All the stuff that made
good bands break up.

07:26.140 --> 07:29.464
But they put all that drama
to good use and wrote great music.

07:29.494 --> 07:32.979
You know, I think I might have
<i>Rumours</i> on LP somewhere.

07:33.031 --> 07:34.915
Oh, everybody does.

07:34.982 --> 07:36.888
I mean, I don't. I sold mine for drugs.

07:36.918 --> 07:38.502
Kidding! Ha! Nope.

07:38.586 --> 07:40.003
I actually did that.

07:40.088 --> 07:41.505
Here we go.

07:41.589 --> 07:44.675
You know, I've wanted to
do a whole lesson devoted

07:44.759 --> 07:48.295
to a single album for a long time.

07:48.346 --> 07:51.431
You know, this is a
really good idea, April.

07:51.499 --> 07:53.801
And I'm here to help.

07:54.925 --> 07:58.337
<i>"Dreams" by Fleetwood Mac</i>

08:05.857 --> 08:09.860
<i>♪ Now, here you go again, you say ♪</i>

08:09.890 --> 08:12.389
<i>♪ you want your freedom ♪</i>

08:13.848 --> 08:18.324
<i>♪ Well who am I to keep you down? ♪</i>

08:21.799 --> 08:25.274
<i>♪ It's only right that you should ♪</i>

08:25.304 --> 08:28.573
<i>♪ play the way you feel it ♪</i>

08:29.321 --> 08:32.059
<i>♪ Listen carefully ♪</i>

08:32.291 --> 08:34.313
<i>♪ to the sound ♪</i>

08:34.754 --> 08:36.777
<i>♪ of your loneliness ♪</i>

08:36.807 --> 08:40.284
<i>- # Like a heartbeat, drives you mad #
- # Heartbeat... #</i>

08:40.784 --> 08:44.270
<i>- # In the stillness of remembering #
- # Stillness... #</i>

08:44.300 --> 08:48.097
<i>- # what you had #
- # Lonely... #</i>

08:48.127 --> 08:50.208
<i>♪ and what you lost ♪</i>

08:52.001 --> 08:54.211
<i>♪ And what you had ♪</i>

08:56.112 --> 08:58.026
<i>♪ and what you lost ♪</i>

09:01.193 --> 09:06.193
<i>♪ Thunder only happens
when it's raining ♪</i>

09:08.872 --> 09:12.048
<i>♪ Players only love you ♪</i>

09:12.078 --> 09:15.130
<i>♪ when they're playing ♪</i>

09:16.372 --> 09:18.880
<i>♪ I say, women, they will ♪</i>

09:18.910 --> 09:22.303
<i>♪ come and they will go ♪</i>

09:25.063 --> 09:30.063
<i>♪ When the rain washes
you clean you'll know ♪</i>

09:32.523 --> 09:34.447
<i>♪ You'll know ♪</i>

