09:52.193 --> 09:54.845
<i>Rumours--</i> a classic
record by Fleetwood Mac.

09:54.896 --> 09:56.751
One of the greatest albums of all time.

09:56.781 --> 09:59.108
Written as the band
was breaking apart...

09:59.611 --> 10:00.698
to keep it together.

10:00.728 --> 10:04.538
Now, this week, we are done with
the backstabbing and the gossip,

10:04.622 --> 10:07.760
and we're channeling all that
energy into working together.

10:08.324 --> 10:11.361
So, pick a song from the album,
put your own spin on it.

10:11.413 --> 10:12.863
Simple as that.

10:20.649 --> 10:23.151
What's going on with you and Santana?

10:23.202 --> 10:24.369
Nothing.

10:24.453 --> 10:27.372
It doesn't sound like nothing.
It sounds like something,

10:27.402 --> 10:28.811
which is almost always
more than nothing.

10:28.841 --> 10:30.479
(Chuckles) I'm down, Artie.

10:30.509 --> 10:31.843
Are you cheating on me with her?

10:31.927 --> 10:34.691
No, of course not. I mean...
I can't. She's a girl.

10:34.835 --> 10:36.560
Fooling around with her isn't cheating.

10:36.590 --> 10:38.301
It's just friends talking with
their tongues super close.

10:38.331 --> 10:39.849
- Who told you that?
- Santana.

10:39.879 --> 10:41.911
Don't you see that
she's manipulating you?

10:41.941 --> 10:43.448
That's not cheating either.
She told me that.

10:43.478 --> 10:45.373
Do you see what's going on here?

10:45.441 --> 10:46.929
You're the hottest girl in this school,

10:47.002 --> 10:49.586
and I wear saddle shoes
on legs that don't work.

10:49.781 --> 10:52.353
This shouldn't be happening.

10:52.383 --> 10:53.985
Not because I'm in a wheelchair

10:54.104 --> 10:55.576
but because I'm obsessed
with Angry Birds

10:55.628 --> 10:56.878
and my mom cuts my hair.

10:56.945 --> 10:57.998
I like your haircut.

10:58.028 --> 11:00.307
It's hard enough for me to
believe that this is real.

11:00.426 --> 11:01.799
If I know that you spend even

11:01.829 --> 11:04.845
a little time sharing
yourself with someone else...

11:04.875 --> 11:07.679
that there's one other person in
your life that can provide

11:07.709 --> 11:10.879
for you the things that
I'm supposed to provide,

11:10.909 --> 11:14.382
it's just too much
for me to take.

11:14.412 --> 11:16.830
And Santana knows that.

11:16.860 --> 11:19.117
She's taking advantage of it
to break us up.

11:19.201 --> 11:21.736
No. Everybody thinks she's
a bad person, but she's not.

11:21.787 --> 11:23.404
God, Brittany,
why are you so stupid?!

11:27.386 --> 11:30.064
You were the only person at this school
that never called me that!

11:39.221 --> 11:42.866
(playing "Never Going
Back Again")

11:43.049 --> 11:46.978
♪ She broke down and let me in ♪

11:54.070 --> 11:57.239
♪ Made me see where I've been ♪

12:06.416 --> 12:11.420
♪ Been down one time,
been down two times ♪

12:14.307 --> 12:16.425
♪ I'm never going back again ♪

12:18.928 --> 12:21.980
♪ Mmm... mmm-mmm... ♪

12:46.322 --> 12:48.206
♪ Mmm... mmm-mmm... ♪

12:48.291 --> 12:51.543
♪ You don't know
what it means to win ♪

12:59.018 --> 13:03.472
♪ Come down and see me again ♪

13:12.031 --> 13:14.616
♪ Been down one time ♪

13:14.683 --> 13:16.535
♪ Been down two times ♪

13:18.321 --> 13:21.523
♪ Mmm, never going back again ♪

13:23.859 --> 13:27.378
♪ Mmm... mmm-mmm... ♪

13:39.092 --> 13:40.509
Stakeout.

13:40.560 --> 13:41.726
So exciting.

13:41.811 --> 13:43.512
It's like an episode
of <i>Hart to Hart.</i>

13:43.563 --> 13:45.514
No, this is not fun or cool.

13:45.565 --> 13:47.715
Then why did you agree
to do it?

13:47.767 --> 13:50.685
Because Quinn cheated
on me with Puck,

13:50.753 --> 13:52.571
and then she cheated
on Sam with me.

13:52.655 --> 13:54.940
I just want to be sure.

13:55.024 --> 13:57.526
I never understood why
you got back with her.

13:57.577 --> 14:00.228
I mean, if you can't
even trust her.

14:02.031 --> 14:05.383
I don't know.

14:05.451 --> 14:07.369
I do.

14:07.420 --> 14:09.254
Because you forgive
your first love anything.

14:12.675 --> 14:15.410
Do you believe in that
thing called karma?

14:15.461 --> 14:16.711
Uh, yeah.

14:18.197 --> 14:19.981
Can you explain it to me?

14:20.049 --> 14:23.135
Uh, well, it's the law
of physics

14:23.219 --> 14:24.603
whereby, for example,

14:24.687 --> 14:26.138
if you do something
to hurt someone,

14:26.222 --> 14:28.273
well, then the laws
of the universe will work

14:28.357 --> 14:29.641
against you until you get hurt.

14:29.725 --> 14:30.942
While we're here,
have you given

14:31.027 --> 14:32.561
any thought to my duet ideas?

14:42.071 --> 14:44.673
I can't believe Kurt
would do that to Blaine.

14:54.018 --> 14:55.418
What do we know
about Sam anyway?

14:55.469 --> 14:57.588
I mean, what town is he from?
What state?

14:58.084 --> 14:59.255
What's his old school like?

14:59.306 --> 15:01.390
Maybe he's a serial killer.
You guys,

15:01.458 --> 15:03.759
I'm telling you,
Kurt wouldn't cheat on Blaine.

15:03.810 --> 15:05.344
It's just like
the <i>Rumours</i> album.

15:05.429 --> 15:07.813
I mean, being apart or on the
road is hard for two artists.

15:07.898 --> 15:09.732
Performers have this "love the
one you're with" mentality.

15:09.799 --> 15:11.350
I mean, look at all of us.

15:11.435 --> 15:13.069
Look at all the different
combinations that we've had.

15:13.136 --> 15:14.654
Finnchel, Puckleberry.

15:14.738 --> 15:16.853
McTina Cohen Chang-Chang.
Artittany.

15:16.883 --> 15:17.973
Pizes.

15:18.289 --> 15:21.494
Guys, we're sitting here
squabbling over what? A rumor.

15:21.578 --> 15:23.440
Finn's right.
We need more information.

15:23.470 --> 15:24.613
I don't want to get into it,

15:25.113 --> 15:27.773
but all I'm gonna say...
Sam's not gay.

15:35.404 --> 15:37.525
God, I'm so sad.

15:37.555 --> 15:40.520
Like a sad little panda.

15:40.768 --> 15:42.576
Well, that's why
I brought you here...

15:42.792 --> 15:45.166
to cheer you up.

15:45.217 --> 15:47.034
I've been going through
that <i>Rumours</i> album

15:47.086 --> 15:48.682
and I found the best song
that really goes

15:48.712 --> 15:50.588
one step past "Landslide"

15:50.673 --> 15:52.974
in expressing my
feelings for you.

15:53.041 --> 15:56.377
My... private feelings.

15:56.428 --> 15:58.179
What about him?

15:58.230 --> 15:59.951
He's just furniture.

15:59.981 --> 16:01.940
Sorry. No offense.

16:01.970 --> 16:03.184
Hit it.

16:03.235 --> 16:05.937
("Songbird" playing)

16:12.919 --> 16:16.252
♪ For you... ♪

16:16.663 --> 16:20.966
♪ There'll be no more crying ♪

16:23.086 --> 16:26.839
♪ For you... ♪

16:26.890 --> 16:31.477
♪ The sun will be shining ♪

16:33.603 --> 16:38.550
♪ And I feel that
when I'm with you ♪

16:38.602 --> 16:41.587
♪ It's all right ♪

16:42.822 --> 16:47.693
♪ I know it's right ♪

16:48.819 --> 16:53.115
♪ And the songbirds
are singing ♪

16:53.199 --> 16:57.453
♪ Like they know the score ♪

16:59.572 --> 17:03.959
♪ And I love you, I love you,
I love you ♪

17:04.044 --> 17:07.396
♪ Like never before ♪

17:09.731 --> 17:14.637
♪ And I wish you all the love ♪

17:14.721 --> 17:18.423
♪ In the world ♪

17:20.777 --> 17:23.228
♪ But most of all ♪

17:23.280 --> 17:28.951
♪ I wish it from myself ♪

17:30.671 --> 17:34.657
♪ And the songbirds
keep singing ♪

17:34.741 --> 17:39.444
♪ Like they know the score ♪

17:41.052 --> 17:45.250
♪ And I love you, I love you,
I love you ♪

17:45.302 --> 17:49.672
♪ Like never before ♪

17:49.756 --> 17:54.393
♪ Like never before. ♪

18:04.129 --> 18:05.427
That was beautiful.

18:08.190 --> 18:09.525
Okay, so why couldn't you

18:09.609 --> 18:11.610
sing that to me
in front of everyone

18:11.661 --> 18:13.195
now that Artie and I
aren't together?

18:13.279 --> 18:14.790
No, not-not yet.

18:15.028 --> 18:18.450
I'm not ready for that type
of public announcement.

18:18.501 --> 18:20.619
Ever since
that <i>Muckraker</i> thing,

18:20.670 --> 18:23.288
people have already started
treating me differently.

18:23.340 --> 18:25.307
I got asked
to join the golf team.

18:25.736 --> 18:27.426
Well, what if I went first?

18:28.201 --> 18:30.252
Come on <i>Fondue for Two.</i>

18:30.468 --> 18:32.230
I'll ask you out to prom

18:32.260 --> 18:34.299
and I'll tell you how I feel,

18:34.351 --> 18:36.919
and all you have
to do is say yes.

18:38.545 --> 18:39.545
Okay.

18:40.059 --> 18:41.059
Yeah.

18:57.146 --> 18:58.146
Stop it.

18:58.230 --> 18:58.980
Stop what?

18:59.064 --> 19:00.531
I am begging you. Sam is cute,

19:00.599 --> 19:01.932
but he's not worth losing
Blaine over.

19:01.984 --> 19:03.568
Oh, how I've missed
your insanity.

19:03.619 --> 19:05.153
He's wearing your jacket, Kurt.

19:05.237 --> 19:07.572
I remember that jacket.
You wore it April of last year.

19:07.623 --> 19:09.240
You said it was
your Earth Day jacket

19:09.291 --> 19:11.042
because it was made out
of recycled hemp.

19:11.109 --> 19:12.543
I know how these things work.

19:12.611 --> 19:14.162
I remember when Finn
and I used to date.

19:14.246 --> 19:15.946
Sometimes he would leave his
letterman jacket at my house,

19:15.998 --> 19:17.632
and I'd wear it to
school the next day.

19:17.716 --> 19:20.284
Okay, you need to bone up on
your Fleetwood Macology.

19:20.335 --> 19:21.469
When they made <i>Rumours,</i>

19:21.553 --> 19:22.753
they weren't speaking
to each other.

19:22.805 --> 19:25.089
Not even "Pass the
nondairy creamer."

19:25.140 --> 19:27.008
They only spoke
about the music.

19:27.092 --> 19:28.593
And it was that focus
that allowed them

19:28.644 --> 19:29.793
to make their masterpiece.

19:29.845 --> 19:31.062
You're deflecting.

19:31.129 --> 19:33.231
No, I'm being a team player,
and any minute spent

19:33.298 --> 19:35.349
on this vicious, hurtful
and hateful gossip

19:35.434 --> 19:38.319
is a minute taken away
from preparing for Nationals.

19:44.827 --> 19:47.862
Why would she say that thing
about Sam not being gay?

19:47.930 --> 19:49.664
She was so sure about it.

19:49.731 --> 19:51.682
Well, they did date.

19:51.750 --> 19:54.001
Yeah, but the way
she said it--

19:54.069 --> 19:55.620
there was something
else going on.

19:55.671 --> 19:59.790
The problem with dating Quinn,
besides the mood swings,

19:59.842 --> 20:01.676
is that she's so...

20:01.760 --> 20:03.911
protective about her feelings.

20:03.979 --> 20:06.364
You never quite know where
you stand with her.

20:06.431 --> 20:08.216
Girls like that do that
to keep their power.

20:08.283 --> 20:09.617
You never did that.

20:09.685 --> 20:11.602
I always knew what
you were thinking.

20:14.890 --> 20:15.723
(door opens)

20:17.276 --> 20:20.311
♪ And if you don't love me now ♪

20:20.362 --> 20:23.731
♪ You will never love me again ♪

20:23.815 --> 20:27.318
♪ I can still hear you sayin' ♪

20:27.369 --> 20:29.220
♪ You would never break
the chain ♪

20:29.288 --> 20:31.789
♪ <i>Never break the chain.</i> ♪

20:34.608 --> 20:36.075
Mr. Shue, thank you
for being

20:36.143 --> 20:37.276
my first interview

20:37.328 --> 20:38.494
for <i>The Muckraker.</i>
To be honest,

20:38.579 --> 20:40.346
I had no idea you were
the journalist type.

20:40.414 --> 20:42.314
Yeah, I have a talk show on
the Internet,

20:42.366 --> 20:44.250
and the comments say that
my questions are too gossipy.

20:44.318 --> 20:46.035
So I joined

20:46.120 --> 20:47.537
the school newspaper to learn

20:47.621 --> 20:48.705
to ask the more hard-hitting
questions.

20:48.789 --> 20:50.089
That's fantastic, Brittany.

20:50.157 --> 20:53.009
So, question one:
boxers or briefs?

20:54.327 --> 20:56.429
Uh, boxers.

20:56.496 --> 20:57.797
Cool.

20:57.848 --> 20:59.999
Okay, question two:
pantyhose or lace panties?

21:00.050 --> 21:02.018
I just said boxers.

21:02.102 --> 21:03.553
Yeah, well, that wasn't
one of the choices,

21:03.637 --> 21:05.288
so I'll just write that you
refused to answer the question.

21:05.356 --> 21:07.774
Brittany, these questions <i>are</i>
sort of gossipy.

21:07.841 --> 21:10.009
Okay, what age did you start
waxing your back?

21:10.060 --> 21:12.362
Brittany, I don't think these
questions are very appropriate.

21:12.446 --> 21:14.013
Well, hard-hitting journalism is
about asking the questions

21:14.064 --> 21:15.415
that people really want to know.

21:15.482 --> 21:17.784
Um, we need to address
some rumors.

21:17.851 --> 21:20.403
How many students
have you had affairs with?

21:20.487 --> 21:23.322
Wait...
There's a rumor about that?

21:23.374 --> 21:24.574
There probably will be now

21:24.658 --> 21:25.375
since you didn't really
answer the question.

21:25.459 --> 21:26.659
None!

21:26.710 --> 21:28.261
Is it the truth
or are you lying? Like when

21:28.328 --> 21:30.880
you didn't give me a straight
answer about the lacy panties.

21:30.964 --> 21:33.299
Brittany, I'm sorry, but I need
to work on some songs.

21:33.366 --> 21:35.418
Are they songs for April Rhodes'
one-woman show?

21:35.502 --> 21:37.536
Yes. Is it because you're
leaving the New Directions?

21:37.588 --> 21:40.372
What?! Because there's a rumor
that you'd rather be on Broadway

21:40.424 --> 21:41.674
than coaching the Glee Club.

21:41.725 --> 21:43.676
Brittany, who gave you
these questions to ask me?

21:43.727 --> 21:45.728
Coach Sylvester said I'm
not at liberty to say.

21:45.796 --> 21:47.764
She told me this before she
finished writing these questions.

21:47.848 --> 21:49.182
I thought so.

21:49.233 --> 21:52.985
All right, Muckrakers, the rumor
mill is up and running.

21:53.053 --> 21:54.153
On to lesson two.

21:54.221 --> 21:56.372
Making... stuff... up.

21:56.440 --> 22:00.392
Jacob, I want you to squeeze
this toothpaste into your hand.

22:00.444 --> 22:02.328
Now put it back in.

22:02.395 --> 22:03.863
Um, I can't.

22:03.914 --> 22:05.498
Exactly.

22:05.565 --> 22:08.618
Oh, no, I didn't! Oh!

22:08.702 --> 22:10.236
SUE:
Fantastic, Azimio.

22:10.287 --> 22:12.422
Now my point, ladies
and gentlemen, is that

22:12.506 --> 22:14.540
once a story is out,
it's out forever.

22:14.591 --> 22:16.542
You can't put it back in.

22:16.593 --> 22:19.212
All right, Muckrakers,
we have a deadline.

22:19.263 --> 22:20.179
(bell ringing) All right,
get out of my classroom.

22:20.247 --> 22:21.214
Get out of here!

22:21.265 --> 22:24.050
Brett.
Sue, what are you doing?

22:24.101 --> 22:25.968
Why are you spreading rumors
that I'm leaving McKinley?

22:26.053 --> 22:28.104
Well, William, I'm sure
you don't dispute

22:28.188 --> 22:30.723
that legendary bratwurst
gobbler April Rhodes is in town

22:30.774 --> 22:33.059
and you're helping her
get back to Broadway.

22:33.110 --> 22:34.610
Am I right?
Of course.

22:34.695 --> 22:35.762
But it doesn't mean
I'm leaving the school.

22:35.829 --> 22:39.098
Let me ask you
something, Will: Why?

22:39.166 --> 22:42.718
You know what they say,
"Those who can't, teach."

22:42.786 --> 22:45.621
Turns out
maybe you actually can.

22:45.706 --> 22:48.624
Think about that next time you
prop your butt chin up on

22:48.692 --> 22:50.276
one of those
tiny little face toilets.

22:50.327 --> 22:52.295
Look at it this way, Will.

22:52.379 --> 22:53.779
You'd finally be rid of me.

22:58.727 --> 23:00.395
Extra! Extra!
Read all about it!

23:00.462 --> 23:02.230
Get you <i>Muckraker</i> here!

23:02.297 --> 23:03.314
I vote for Quinn.

23:03.399 --> 23:05.516
Bite me, Fabray.

23:12.016 --> 23:12.918
Finn.

23:13.496 --> 23:14.880
Wait, why are you storming?

23:14.965 --> 23:16.999
I'm the one
who should be storming.

23:17.050 --> 23:18.851
Really? Because the way
I see it, I'm the stormer

23:18.936 --> 23:20.169
and you should be the stormee.

23:20.220 --> 23:22.171
According to today's paper,
"Finn and Rachel

23:22.222 --> 23:25.107
were seen sitting closely, laughing, talking
intimately." We were on a stakeout.

23:25.175 --> 23:27.176
What were you doing
with him in that motel?

23:27.227 --> 23:28.644
I'm not cheating on you.

23:28.695 --> 23:30.279
This time around,
I haven't and I won't.

23:30.347 --> 23:32.014
You have to learn to trust me.

23:32.065 --> 23:33.566
I can't trust you
if you won't tell me the truth.

23:33.650 --> 23:34.984
Well, what were you and Rachel
doing together, huh?

23:35.035 --> 23:37.370
Staking out. That's what
you do on a stakeout.

23:37.454 --> 23:39.238
What were you talking about?
Glee Club, okay?

23:39.323 --> 23:41.377
She wants to do
a duet with me. That's all. Trust me.

23:41.387 --> 23:43.297
Well, then I guess we both have
to learn to trust each other.

23:43.449 --> 23:46.297
- I guess so. - And I guess I know what song
we'll be singing this week in Glee Club

23:46.518 --> 23:50.000
♪ I don't want to know
the reasons why love keeps ♪

23:50.211 --> 23:53.047
♪ Right on
walking on down the line ♪

23:53.281 --> 23:56.423
♪ I don't want to stand
'tween you and love, honey ♪

23:56.564 --> 24:00.236
♪ I just want you
to feel fine ♪

24:00.246 --> 24:03.699
♪ I don't want to know
the reasons why love keeps ♪

24:03.783 --> 24:06.702
♪ Right on
walking on down the line ♪

24:06.827 --> 24:10.280
♪ I don't want to know
the reasons why love keeps ♪

24:10.364 --> 24:13.283
♪ Right on
walking on down the line ♪

24:13.367 --> 24:16.586
♪ I don't want to stand
'tween you and love, honey ♪

24:16.670 --> 24:19.739
♪ I just want you
to feel fine ♪

24:22.008 --> 24:25.427
♪ Finally, baby ♪

24:25.511 --> 24:28.046
♪ The truth has been told ♪

24:28.097 --> 24:32.050
♪ Now you tell me
that I'm crazy ♪

24:32.101 --> 24:35.904
♪ That's nothing
that I didn't know ♪

24:35.988 --> 24:38.056
♪ Trying to survive ♪

24:38.107 --> 24:41.860
♪ Oh, you say you love me,
but you don't know ♪

24:41.911 --> 24:45.364
♪ You got me rockin'
and a-reelin' ♪

24:45.415 --> 24:49.501
♪ Hey, you know what you do ♪

24:49.568 --> 24:53.288
♪ Oh, oh, yeah ♪

24:53.373 --> 24:55.390
♪ Uh-huh ♪

25:04.384 --> 25:10.972
♪ I... ♪

25:11.057 --> 25:15.060
♪ I don't want to know. ♪

25:17.280 --> 25:18.763
(song ends)

25:18.815 --> 25:20.532
(scattered applause)

25:20.599 --> 25:23.768
Okay! Terrific job, guys.

25:23.820 --> 25:25.203
Um, might want to try to smile

25:25.271 --> 25:27.122
a little bit more
next time, though.

25:27.190 --> 25:28.990
Yeah. It was lovely,
but I prefer

25:29.075 --> 25:31.059
Quinn's duet performance
of "Lucky" with Sam better.

25:31.127 --> 25:33.712
Since you and Sam have become
a lot closer lately, maybe

25:33.779 --> 25:34.779
you guys should do duets
together more often.

25:34.831 --> 25:35.881
Where is Sam?

25:35.948 --> 25:37.616
Quinn and Kurt
are both here today,

25:37.683 --> 25:38.800
so we know he's not
doing the dirty.

25:38.885 --> 25:40.585
I know what you're doing.

25:40.636 --> 25:41.837
You want Finn and I
to stop singing together

25:41.921 --> 25:43.722
so that you can sing
with him again.

25:43.789 --> 25:45.640
Frankly, yes. Finn and I have
amazing proven harmonies.

25:45.725 --> 25:46.892
And when it comes to Nationals,

25:46.959 --> 25:48.226
I think it makes more sense

25:48.294 --> 25:49.344
for him to be paired with me.

25:49.429 --> 25:50.979
Well, it's not happening.

25:51.063 --> 25:52.597
Not as long as Finn wants
to be with me.

25:52.648 --> 25:55.150
Wait, I thought you said this
relationship was about trust.

25:55.234 --> 25:58.487
Oh, I trust you.
I just don't trust her.

25:58.571 --> 25:59.821
Quinn, I don't think
you can mandate

25:59.906 --> 26:01.523
who pairs up for
Nationals, all right?

26:01.607 --> 26:03.475
Vocal Adrenaline doesn't need
any help from us.

26:03.526 --> 26:06.061
I love being here,
and I want to win,

26:06.129 --> 26:07.979
but my relationship
comes first.

26:08.047 --> 26:09.698
I'm sorry, but Finn,

26:09.782 --> 26:12.584
if you want to be with me,
no more songs with her.

26:12.651 --> 26:14.085
What?!

26:16.839 --> 26:17.989
(school bell ringing)

26:18.057 --> 26:19.591
(Finn scoffs)

26:19.658 --> 26:22.344
(orchestra plays lush intro)

26:22.428 --> 26:27.215
♪ We took a cab back
to my bachelor pad ♪

26:27.300 --> 26:31.970
♪ I had a feeling
I would see this thing through ♪

26:32.038 --> 26:35.140
♪ My doorman Stan,
he took you by the hand ♪

26:35.191 --> 26:39.010
♪ As he said,
"Right this way, you two" ♪

26:39.061 --> 26:41.229
♪ But you said ♪

26:41.314 --> 26:42.731
♪ Stanley Glover ♪

26:42.815 --> 26:44.866
♪ You were once
my lover! ♪

26:44.951 --> 26:46.351
♪ It's April! ♪

26:46.402 --> 26:49.521
♪ Yeah! I guess
I slept with you! ♪

26:49.572 --> 26:52.324
♪ Because my name
is April Rhodes ♪

26:52.375 --> 26:55.544
♪ I've kissed
princes and toads ♪

26:55.628 --> 26:58.363
♪ And it's a good bet ♪

26:58.414 --> 27:06.087
♪ I've slept with you! ♪

27:06.172 --> 27:11.042
♪ You! ♪

27:11.093 --> 27:13.011
(song ends)

27:13.062 --> 27:14.729
Will!
(laughs)

27:14.814 --> 27:17.148
Will, oh, that
song is fantastic!

27:17.216 --> 27:18.517
It was amazing progress.

27:18.568 --> 27:20.819
I mean, it was emotional,
it was funny, it was...

27:20.886 --> 27:22.354
It's you.

27:22.405 --> 27:24.155
Oh, do this with me, Will.

27:24.223 --> 27:26.074
Help me take this
show to Broadway.

27:26.158 --> 27:30.161
I'm flattered, but I have
to take the kids to Nationals.

27:30.229 --> 27:31.997
A show choir championship?

27:32.064 --> 27:33.865
Yes.
Will, that's their dream.

27:33.916 --> 27:36.117
Yes, at one point,
it was yours and mine,

27:36.202 --> 27:37.586
but look where that got us.

27:37.670 --> 27:41.423
We're standing on
the exact same stage...

27:41.507 --> 27:45.076
wishing that we could have
done something bigger.

27:52.918 --> 27:55.753
♪ Fondue for Two!
Fondue for Two! ♪

27:55.805 --> 27:57.105
♪ That's some hot dish! ♪

27:57.189 --> 27:59.090
♪ Fondue for Two! ♪

27:59.141 --> 28:00.809
Hi. I'm Brittany.

28:00.893 --> 28:03.361
Welcome to <i>Fondue for Two.</i>

28:03.429 --> 28:06.565
My guest today was supposed
to be Santana,

28:06.616 --> 28:08.483
but she texted
about an hour ago,

28:08.568 --> 28:10.118
and it just said, "I can't."

28:10.202 --> 28:12.571
So, show must go on.

28:12.622 --> 28:15.373
Um, I will be interviewing
Lord Tubbington.

28:15.441 --> 28:17.075
Question one:

28:17.143 --> 28:19.327
Do you think <i>The Aristocats</i>
is an accurate portrayal

28:19.412 --> 28:21.379
of the feline relationship?

28:21.447 --> 28:22.547
(purring)

28:22.615 --> 28:24.132
You know, just because

28:24.216 --> 28:25.901
we're doing this interview
doesn't mean

28:25.968 --> 28:28.136
I'm still not mad at you.

28:28.204 --> 28:30.255
'Cause I know
you started smoking again.

28:30.306 --> 28:32.140
(purring)

28:35.886 --> 28:37.854
(school bell ringing)

28:43.773 --> 28:45.931
Emma, did you wash those grapes
at home?

28:45.941 --> 28:47.045
I just rinsed them.

28:47.055 --> 28:48.172
Yeah, I put the whole bunch

28:48.256 --> 28:49.623
in a colander,

28:49.674 --> 28:51.558
and I just let the cold water
run right over them.

28:51.626 --> 28:53.627
For a half hour or so.

28:53.678 --> 28:55.896
Still, Emma, that's amazing.

28:55.963 --> 28:57.181
I've been, um,

28:57.265 --> 28:58.932
taking my medication
for a couple of weeks.

29:00.485 --> 29:03.387
I'm so proud of you, Emma.

29:03.455 --> 29:04.805
You inspired me, Will--

29:04.873 --> 29:06.156
